sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant B as Browser (Audio Element)
    participant FE as UniWorld Frontend (Angular)
    participant API as UniWorld Backend API
    participant AUTH as Auth Service (JWT)
    participant DB as Metadata DB
    participant MEDIA as Media Storage / CDN

    U->>B: Click "Play" on song
    B->>FE: emit playEvent(songId)
    FE->>AUTH: ensure token (optional)
    AUTH-->>FE: token valid (userId)

    FE->>API: GET /api/songs/{id}/stream [Authorization]
    API->>AUTH: validate token
    AUTH-->>API: 200 OK (user)

    API->>DB: fetch song metadata (path, mimeType, rights)
    DB-->>API: metadata

    alt Backend proxies stream
      API->>MEDIA: open file stream (internal)
      MEDIA-->>API: stream bytes (chunked)
      API-->>FE: HTTP 200 chunked response (audio/*)
      FE-->>B: set audio.srcObject(blob/stream) and play
      B-->>B: audio plays (buffering handled by browser)
    else CDN / Signed URL flow
      API->>MEDIA: request signed URL for song file
      MEDIA-->>API: signed URL (time-limited)
      API-->>FE: 200 { streamUrl }
      FE-->>B: audio.src = streamUrl
      B->>MEDIA: GET streamUrl (CORS, Range)
      MEDIA-->>B: stream bytes
      B-->>B: audio plays
    end

    Note over API,FE: Playback telemetry (optional)
    FE->>API: POST /api/telemetry/playback {position, events}
    API->>DB: store telemetry
    DB-->>API: 200 OK

    %% Error handling
    API-->>FE: 401/403 if auth fails
    API-->>FE: 404 if song not found
    MEDIA-->>API: 5xx if media unavailable
    FE-->>B: show error UI / fallback
